{{C Standard Library}}
The '''C date and time functions''' are a group of functions in the [[C standard library|standard library]] of the [[C (programming language)|C programming language]] implementing date and time manipulation operations.<ref>{{cite book | url=http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg14/www/docs/n1124.pdf  | title=ISO/IEC 9899:1999 specification | at=p. 351, § 7.32.2}}</ref> They provide support for [[system time|time]] acquisition, conversion between date formats, and formatted output to strings.

==Overview of functions==

The C date and time operations are defined in the <code>time.h</code> [[header file]] (<code>ctime</code> header in [[C++]]).

